Thoroughly satisfied! The menu is minimal and highlights traditional classics making selection easy. Was able to see my order progress and it came exactly between the estimated delivery time. The food still looked great even though it is packed. Sometimes this can lead to food presentation disaster, but we even got the food on plates and made it look like it was served at the restaurant. I have been to Thailand and surrounding countries and everything from Papa Thai was delicious. 100% positive ratings is hard for even a robot, but "Thank you" for the good experience! 5 stars from me and my friends. (Ordered through GrubHub and got 25% off)

Won’t be ordering from here ever again

Maybe they have other items that are good. We shall see.

Loved all the live plants on the table. The homemade chilli sauce was the perfect balance of sweet, spicy & sour. The lightly battered, perfectly fried calamari had no salt and the batter wasn't seasoned; however the dipping sauce made up for it. My green curry was delicious and the eggplant and melange of vegetables were perfectly cooked in the sauce. My dates pad thai was more on the sweet side but the chilli   paste they brought to the table gave it the spice it needed. I would definitely go back.

I just ordered from here on Uber Eats. Your name is Pad Thai, yet somehow you managed to mess up a signature dish. The chicken Pad Thai I ordered tasted like it came from a can. The noodles were mushy, the sauce was too sweet, and there were only 3 pieces of chicken.

I tried the food here 3x before I rated it. I live close by, so it was kind of by default. The food is bland and subpart compared to other Thai Restaurants. On my last visit I ordered pineapple fried rice, but they should name it "cabbage fried rice" because there was more cabbage than pineapples and cashews.

The $9.99 lunch special was a good price for the quality of food. The soup was delicious and so were the spring rolls. The pad thai was a little sweet for my liking but I would return. I never take the time to write reviews but I'm doing this so they'll do well because I never want them to go away!! First thing I ordered for delivery was their grilled shish kebaba. Came with salad, rice and amazing roasted peppers. I ordered the same for delivery the very next day. I'm ordering it again now. Nice to have you guys, welcome to the neighborhood!!!

We tried falafel, shakshuka and Chicken Tagine with couscous. The chicken was moist and subtly flavored; the falafel were pressed thin, coated in sesame and had a nice coarse texture.  Shakshuka is a difficult dish for take-out; it had less tomato sauce than is common. Overall the food was fresh and satisfying. Although we ordered for pick up, there is a wine menu for dining in and the ambience is simple yet warm. Prices are average for sit-down restaurants in the area.
